# Pull Request Guidelines

Follow these guidelines when creating and reviewing pull requests.

## Branch Naming
- `feature/[feature-name]` for new features
- `fix/[issue-number]-[brief-description]` for bug fixes
- `refactor/[scope]` for code refactoring
- `docs/[scope]` for documentation updates

## PR Title Format
```
type(scope): brief description
```

Types:
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding missing tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

## PR Description Requirements
Your PR description must include:
1. Summary of changes
2. Related issue numbers
3. Breaking changes (if any)
4. Testing performed
5. Code review checklist completed

## Code Review Requirements
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] No merge conflicts
- [ ] Code follows style guidelines
- [ ] Documentation is updated
- [ ] Changes are atomic and focused
- [ ] AI PR Review completed successfully

## Review Process
1. Submit PR
2. Wait for AI PR Review
3. Address AI feedback
4. Request human review
5. Address reviewer comments
6. Get approval
7. Merge

## CI Requirements
- All CI checks must pass:
  - pytest (unit tests)
  - black (formatting)
  - isort (import sorting)
  - flake8 (linting)
  - mypy (type checking)
  - pytest-cov (coverage)

## Version Control
- Follow semantic versioning
- Keep commit messages clear and descriptive
- Reference issue numbers in commits when applicable

